## Results with Perihelion Compression Scaling

### Single-Body Objects

#### Mercury (r₀/a = 0.794, ε_single = 0.065 × 0.794^(-2.5) = 0.16)
| Method | Prediction (yr) | Error (%) |
|--------|----------------|-----------|
| Kepler | 0.241 | 0.0% |
| MBT-Compression | 4.959 × 0.307 × 0.16 = **0.244** | **+1.2%** |
| Hybrid (w_geom=0.905) | 0.905×0.241 + 0.095×0.244 = **0.241** | **0.0%** |

*Perfect fit achieved!*

#### Venus (r₀/a = 0.993, ε_single = 0.065 × 0.993^(-2.5) = 0.066)
